Analysis of the Target Image

There are two separate “towers” in the main image:

• Left Tower (5 layers total)  
  1) Bottom layer: two horizontal orange cylinders side by side.  
  2) Above them: one green rectangular prism bridging across the cylinders.  
  3) Above the green block: one red cube.  
  4) Above the red cube: one blue cube.  
  5) Top: one orange triangular “roof” block.  

• Right Tower (4 layers total)  
  1) Bottom layer: two cubes side by side (left is orange, right is blue).  
  2) Above those: two cubes side by side (left is blue, right is orange).  
  3) Above that second row of cubes: one green rectangular prism bridging across them.  
  4) Top: one orange triangular “roof” block.  

Required Blocks from the Dictionary

Match each shape/color/orientation exactly (no rotations are allowed):

• For the Left Tower  
  – Orange cylinder (horizontal): index 10 → 2 copies  
  – Green rectangular block (horizontal): index 5 → 1 copy  
  – Red cube: index 4 → 1 copy  
  – Blue cube: index 1 → 1 copy  
  – Orange triangular roof block: index 14 → 1 copy  

• For the Right Tower  
  – Orange cube: index 3 → 2 copies  
  – Blue cube: index 1 → 2 copies  
  – Green rectangular block (horizontal): index 5 → 1 copy  
  – Orange triangular roof block: index 14 → 1 copy  

Assembly Instructions

Use the following step‐by‐step sequence (you may interleave them in any logical build order; here is one illustrative order):

{
  Step1: Move block with index 10
  Step2: Move block with index 10
  Step3: Move block with index 5
  Step4: Move block with index 4
  Step5: Move block with index 1
  Step6: Move block with index 14
  Step7: Move block with index 3
  Step8: Move block with index 1
  Step9: Move block with index 1
  Step10: Move block with index 3
  Step11: Move block with index 5
  Step12: Move block with index 14
}
